      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments completed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "A second qualified FEA analyst independently reviewed the model setup, loading and boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material card assignments. Discrepancies were resolved prior to final runs. Use error controls are adequate."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-form-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening Ti-6Al-4V) validated against coupon tensile data; contact formulation consistent with ASTM F1717 fixture geometry.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening parameters for Ti-6Al-4V were fit to coupon tensile test data from the same material lot. Augmented Lagrange contact was applied at screw-rod and screw-vertebral body block interfaces, consistent with the F1717 fixture. Model form fidelity is sufficient for the QoIs of interest."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/model-inputs-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements; material properties from coupon testing of same lot; torque preload from calibrated torque wrench records.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry was digitized via CMM with ±0.01 mm accuracy. Material elastic modulus and yield strength were derived from five coupon tests per lot. Rod pre-torque was measured with a calibrated wrench and applied as an equivalent bolt-load boundary condition. Input uncertainty is quantified and propagated."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-samples-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lot; sample dimensions verified by CMM prior to testing.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were drawn from a single production lot and tested across two independent laboratories (6 + 5 constructs). CMM verification confirmed dimensional conformance. Sample size exceeds the minimum required for statistical comparison."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-conditions-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed at multiple load levels and at least two independent laboratories with environmental controls documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at both participating laboratories under ambient temperature conditions consistent with ASTM F1717. Load frame calibration records were current for both sites. While inter-laboratory variability was characterized, testing was performed at a single axial offset load level (10 mm offset, 150 N axial preload) rather than the multiple loading configurations that would be needed to fully characterize the test condition space. Engineering judgment supports that the single condition is representative of the clinical loading scenario, and the overall QoI agreement provides confidence in the model predictions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/equiv-inputs-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) traceable to measured experimental values; equivalency table documented.",
      "rationale": "An equivalency table was prepared mapping each experimental parameter (screw dimensions, rod diameter, block geometry, torque, axial preload, offset) to the corresponding model input value and its source measurement. All parameters are within ±2% of measured experimental values."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/output-comparison-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI differences <10% and E/uval <1.96 for all three quantities of interest across N=11 constructs.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were compared to experimental means. Maximum QoI difference was 6.8% (yield force). E/uval statistics were 0.91, 1.12, and 0.78 for the three QoIs, all below the 1.96 threshold. Acceptance criteria are met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-qoi-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
